# ğŸ§  Perceptron Basics (Deep Learning Concept)

## ğŸ“Œ What is Perceptron?

The Perceptron is the **simplest neural network model** and the foundation of Deep Learning.
It works like a single artificial neuron that decides whether an input belongs to a class or not.

ğŸ‘‰ It is mainly used for **Binary Classification** (Yes/No, True/False, Churn/Not Churn)

Example in this project:
Predict â†’ Will customer leave the company?

---

## âš™ï¸ How Perceptron Works

A perceptron takes inputs, multiplies them with weights, adds bias and passes result through an activation function.

### Mathematical Formula

z = w1x1 + w2x2 + w3x3 + ... + b

Output:
If z â‰¥ 0 â†’ 1 (Positive Class)
If z < 0 â†’ 0 (Negative Class)

---

## ğŸ§© Components of Perceptron

* Inputs (x) â†’ Customer features (tenure, charges, contract)
* Weights (w) â†’ Importance of each feature
* Bias (b) â†’ Threshold adjuster
* Activation Function â†’ Decision maker (Step Function)

---

## ğŸ“Š Simple Example

Suppose we predict churn using 2 features:

* Monthly Charges
* Tenure

Weights:
w1 = 0.6
w2 = -0.4
b = -2

Customer Data:
Monthly Charges = 80
Tenure = 12

Calculation:
z = (0.6 Ã— 80) + (-0.4 Ã— 12) - 2
z = 48 - 4.8 - 2
z = 41.2

Since z > 0 â†’ Output = 1 â†’ Customer will churn

---

## ğŸ“‰ Limitation of Perceptron

Perceptron can only solve **linearly separable problems**.
It fails when data is complex (real world customer behavior is complex).

That is why we use:
â¡ï¸ Multi-Layer Neural Network (Deep Learning)

---

## ğŸ”— Relation to This Project

Customer churn prediction is not simple linear behavior.
So instead of single perceptron we use **multiple neurons (ANN)** which learn complex patterns from customer data.

Perceptron = 1 neuron
Deep Learning = many neurons working together

---

## ğŸ¯ Key Takeaway

Perceptron is the building block of neural networks.
Understanding perceptron helps understand how Deep Learning models make decisions.
